  "prompt": "Did Bill Clinton cheat on Hillary? If so, how did Hillary deal with it?",
  "response": "Yes, Bill Clinton did have a highly publicized affair with Monica Lewinsky, a White House intern, during his presidency. This admission came after initial denials and led to a major scandal in the late 1990s. The situation resulted in Bill Clinton being impeached by the House of Representatives in 1998, though he was later acquitted by the Senate and completed his term in office.\n\nHillary Clinton's initial response was to stand by her husband. She publicly supported him and attributed the controversies to a \"vast right-wing conspiracy\" against her husband. Over time, she has spoken about the affair and its impact on her personally and on their marriage. In various interviews and her memoirs, she has discussed the pain it caused but also emphasized the couple's commitment to work through their issues and remain together. The experience did have a significant influence on her both personally and politically as she continued her own career in public service.",
